The TIP has some members of other ethnicities besides the Uighur, a TIP suicide bomber in Afghanistan who attacked American troops was Nuruddin, a Turkish militant and he advocated that Turks and Uighurs mount "Islamic flags at the White House and Beijing's Tiananmen Square" while a TIP Kazakh member named Uspan Batir made an appearance in a video and said

{{quote|text=There is a line artificially drawn by the infidel in between us—saying you are from Kazakhstan, Turkistan, Uzbekistan and Kyrgyzstan—there is a line drawn artificially by the infidel, my brothers . . . The religion never came only to Kazakhs, it did not come only to Uighurs, and it did not come only to Arabs . . . Do not separate. Allah said, you do not separate to say that 'you are Kazakhstan, you are Turkistan and you are Uzbekistan.'<ref name="hudson1"/>}}

The Turkish TIP suicide bomber Nuruddin called for expulsion of "Crusader" and "Buddhist" "infidels", and called "Andalusia, East Turkistan, Chechnya, South Africa" as "lands of Islam".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doguturkistanbulteni.com/2015/10/02/turkistan-islam-cemaatinden-turkiyeli-muslumanlara-nasihat/ |title=Türkistan İslam Cemaati'nden Türkiyeli Müslümanlara Nasihat |work=Doğu Türkistan Bülteni Haber Ajansı |date=2 October 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022161308/http://www.doguturkistanbulteni.com/2015/10/02/turkistan-islam-cemaatinden-turkiyeli-muslumanlara-nasihat/ |archivedate=22 October 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Nuruddin said that Allah "blesses" the "Jihad" in Somalia, Iraq, Chechnya, Yemen and other places and that the "Muslim Mujahideen" were fighting NATO and America.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doguturkistanbulteni.com/2015/10/23/turkistan-islam-cemaati-nden-mucahitleri-elestirenlere-nasihat/ |title=Türkistan İslam Cemaati'nden Mücahitleri Eleştirenlere Nasihat |work=Doğu Türkistan Bülteni Haber Ajansı |date=23 October 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304075348/http://www.doguturkistanbulteni.com/2015/10/23/turkistan-islam-cemaati-nden-mucahitleri-elestirenlere-nasihat/ |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ummetislam.org/turkistan-islam-cemaati-mucahidi-sehit-nureddin-el-kurdiden-mucahitleri-elestirenlere-nasihat |title=Türkistan İslam Cemaati Şehidi Nureddin el-Kürdî'den Mücahidleri Eleştirenlere Nasihat |work=Ümmet-i İslam |date=17 April 2015}}</ref> Nuruddin asked for more Turkish foreign fighters.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.siteintelgroup.com/Jihadist-News/suicide-bomber-calls-turkish-muslims-to-the-battlefield-in-tip-video.html |title=Suicide Bomber Calls Turkish Muslims to the Battlefield in TIP Video |work=Jihadist Threat |publisher=SITE Intelligence Group |date=15 January 2014}}</ref> He also asked for funding from Turkish people.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.siteintelgroup.com/Jihadist-News/tip-fighter-urges-muslims-in-turkey-to-contribute-to-jihad.html |title=TIP Fighter Urges Muslims in Turkey to Contribute to Jihad |work=Jihadist Threat |publisher=SITE Intelligence Group |date=15 January 2014}}</ref> In Afghanistan there are other Turkish members of TIP.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.siteintelgroup.com/Jihadist-News/tip-video-shows-training-attacks-of-turkish-fighters-in-afghanistan.html |title=TIP Video Shows Training, Attacks of Turkish Fighters in Afghanistan |work=Jihadist Threat |publisher=SITE Intelligence Group |date=15 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.siteintelgroup.com/Jihadist-News/tip-video-shows-attacks-gives-memorial-for-slain-official-abdul-aziz.html |title=TIP Video Shows Attacks, Gives Memorial for Slain Official Abdul Aziz |work=Jihadist Threat |publisher=SITE Intelligence Group |date=15 January 2014}}</ref> Ebu Bekir Et Turki committed the suicide attack along with Nuruddin.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Dogu_Turkistan_/status/664441733808300033 |title=Account Suspended}}{{dead link|date=May 2016}}</ref> TIP released a video of the TIP fighters Usame El Kurdi and Ebu Bekir Turki singing a nasheed in Afghanistan.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Dogu_turkistan0/status/714757819346628608 |title=Account Suspended}}{{dead link|date=May 2016}}</ref> A TIP member from Kazakhstan called Abduşşehit Turkistani was killed in Afghanistan.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doguturkistanbulteni.com/2016/03/23/turkistan-islam-cemaati-mucahidi-sehit-abdussehid-turkistaninin-hayati/ |title=Türkistan İslam Cemaati Mücahidi Şehit Abduşşehit Turkistani'nin Hayatı |publisher=Doğu Türkistan Bülteni Haber Ajansı |date=23 March 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326200947/http://www.doguturkistanbulteni.com/2016/03/23/turkistan-islam-cemaati-mucahidi-sehit-abdussehid-turkistaninin-hayati/ |archivedate=26 March 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Dogu_turkistan0/status/712749936115363840 |title=Account Suspended}}{{dead link|date=June 2016}}</ref> Nuruddin called for the destruction of other religions and for the world to be dominated by Islam.<ref>{{cite news |first=Bill |last=Roggio |title=Turkistan Islamic Party touts suicide bombings in Afghanistan |work=Long War Journal |date=26 May 2013 |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2013/05/turkistan_islamic_pa_3.php}}</ref>

With the goal of establishing a Central Asian Islamic state, Uyghurs, Chechens, Uzbeks, Tajiks, Kyrgyz Kazakhs, and other ethnicities flocked to serve under Islamic Movement of Uzbekistan leader [[Juma Namangani]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Ahmed |last=Rashid |title=They're Only Sleeping: Why militant Islamicists in Central Asia aren't going to go away. |date=14 January 2002 |work=[[The New Yorker]] |url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2002/01/14/theyre-only-sleeping}}</ref>

The Turkistan Islamic Party in Syria uses the [[Jihadist black flag|Jihadist Shahada flag]] with the name of the group in Arabic below the shahada: (الحزب الإسلامي التركستاني لنصرة أهل الشام) "Turkistan Islamic Party for the Support of the People of [[Bilad al-Sham|al-Sham]]". TIP in Syria also calls itself by the name of "Turkistan Islamic Party in the land of al-Sham" (الحزب الإسلامي التركستاني في بلاد الشام). A Jabhat al Nusra member named Abu Rabah helped Uyghur militants start their first camp in Syria and a Turkish language website based in Turkey was launched to recruit "Uyghur mujahideen" to fight in Syria for the Al-Qaeda affiliated Uyghur Turkistan Islamic Party.<ref>{{cite news|last= |first= |date=2015-05-19 |title=الصينيون الأويغور... "انغماسيّو أردوغان" الجدد |url=http://asraar-sy.com/?content=3&id_new=30017 |newspaper=أسرار |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124140443/http://asraar-sy.com/?content=3&id_new=30017 |archivedate=24 January 2016 |df=dmy }}</ref> TIP (ETIM) sent the "Turkistan Brigade" ([[Katibat Turkistani]]) (Arabic:كتيبة تركستاني) to take part in the [[Syrian Civil War]],<ref name="turkestan">{{cite web |url=https://news.siteintelgroup.com/Jihadist-News/tip-division-in-syria-releases-video-promoting-cause-inciting-for-jihad.html |title=TIP Division in Syria Releases Video Promoting Cause, Inciting for Jihad |work=Jihadist Threat |publisher=SITE Intelligence Group |date=6 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://archive.org/details/Tuba4Ilan1 |title=Tuba 4 Ilan 1 |work=Internet Archive |date=18 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://archive.org/details/Raziman |title=Raziman |work=Internet Archive |date=23 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://archive.org/details/mensure |title=mensure |work=Internet Archive |date=31 August 2015}}</ref> most noticeably in the [[2015 Jisr al-Shughur offensive]].<ref>{{cite AV media |title=A short video showing the opening of yesterdays ongoing battle in Jisr ash-Shugur |date=22 April 2015 |work=YouTube |author=Junud Ash Sham |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JEnv694zinM}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Weiss |first=Caleb |title=Turkistan Islamic Party in Syria involved in new Idlib offensive |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/04/turkistan-islamic-party-in-syria-involved-in-new-idlib-offensive.php |work=Long War Journal |date=23 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Turkistan Islamic Party had significant role in recent Idlib offensive |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/04/turkistan-islamic-party-had-significant-role-recent-idlib-offensive.php |website=Long War Journal |date=30 April 2015 |first=Caleb |last=Weiss}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.siteintelgroup.com/Jihadist-News/tip-division-in-syria-releases-video-on-its-participation-in-jisr-al-shughour.html |title=TIP Division in Syria Releases Video on its Participation in Jisr al-Shughour |work=Jihadist Threat |publisher=SITE Intelligence Group |date=1 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |url=http://www.liveleak.com/view?i=cb1_1430611230 |title=Turkistan/Chechnya group releases combat footage of capture of Jsir Shurour |work=LiveLeak.com |date=2 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |url=http://www.liveleak.com/view?i=c10_1438594302 |title=[Combat edit] NEW Hizb al-Islami at-Turkistan release - Routing SAA brigade from a city in Idlib (August, 2015) |work=LiveLeak.com |date=3 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://thelineofsteel.weebly.com/analysis/turkistan-islamic-party-in-syria-fighting-alongside-junud-al-sham-in-idlib |title=Turkistan Islamic Party in Syria fighting alongside Junud al Sham in Idlib   |work=The Line of Steel |date=24 April 2015}}</ref>{{citekill|date=March 2017}} Al-Qaeda linked groups in Syria include the Syrian branch of the Chechen Caucasus Emirate, Uzbek militants, and the Turkistan Islamic Party.<ref>{{cite news |last=Joscelyn |first=Thomas |title=US counterterrorism efforts in Syria: A winning strategy? |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/09/us-counterterrorism-efforts-in-syria-a-winning-strategy.php |work=Long War Journal |date=29 September 2015}}</ref> The leader of TIP (ETIM) in Syria was Abu Rida al-Turkestani (أبو رضا التركستاني).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/syria-the-epicenter-of-future-jihad |title=Syria: The Epicenter of Future Jihad |last=Zelin |first=Aaron Y. |date=30 June 2014 |publisher=The Washington Institute}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://thelineofsteel.weebly.com/news/turkestan-islamic-party-in-syria |title=Turkestan Islamic Party in Syria |work=The Line of Steel |date=27 December 2014}}</ref> Abu Rida Al-Turkestani gave a speech during the offensive in Jisr al-Shughur inviting "Muslims" from "East Turkestan" to come to Sham in order to "kill" "Nusayris" (Alawites).<ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://archive.org/details/ghiriblargha-jennet-bolsun4-kisim |title=ghiriblargha-jennet-bolsun4-kisim |work=Internet Archive |date=22 August 2015}}</ref> Abu Rida al-Turkestani gave a speech denouncing America and claiming Muslims are oppressed "in the land of Afghanistan, and in Turkestan, and in Waziristan, and in Burma, and in Bilad ash-Sham"<ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://archive.org/details/qrba_tobaaa1 |title=طوبى للغرباء 1 : |work=Internet Archive |date=25 August 2015}}</ref> In May 2015 in Jisr al-Shugour the Syrian army killed Abu Rida al-Turkestani near a hospital.<ref>{{cite news |date=26 May 2015 |title=مقتل المتزعم العسكري لما يسمى ''الحزب الاسلامي التركستاني'' في الاشتباكات مع الجيش السوري في محيط مشفى جسر الشغور |url=http://www.alahednews.com.lb/fastnews/273934/مقتل-المتزعم-العسكري-لما-يسمى-الحزب-الاسلامي-التركستاني-في-الاشتباكات-مع-الجيش-السوري-في-محيط |work=Al-Ahed News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=خــاص |date=26 May 2015 |title=تفاصيل: الجيش السوري يقتل أحد أبرز قادة "القاعدة" العسكريين |url=http://www.alhadathnews.net/archives/157704 |newspaper=الحدث نيوز }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://thelineofsteel.weebly.com/news/turkestan-islamic-party-fighters-killed-in-syria |title=Turkistan Islamic Party Fighters Killed In Syria   |work=The Line of Steel |date=19 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |user=lamloma3 |number=603210273378279426 |title=تم دعس الخنزير ابو رضا التركستاني قائد ما يسمى الحزب الاسلامي التركستاني التابع لجبهة النصرة في جسر الشغور بريف ادلب |date=26 May 2015}}</ref> TIP (ETIM) members in Syria fight alongside the Al-Qaeda branch [[al-Nusra Front|Al Nusrah Front]] since TIP is allied to Al-Qaeda in Pakistan and Afghanistan and conducted suicide bombings for Nusrah Front.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thelineofsteel.weebly.com/news/more-on-turkestan-islamic-party-in-syria |title=More on Turkestan Islamic Party in Syria |work=The Line of Steel |date=1 January 2015}}</ref> The Turkistan Islamic Party (Uighur), Al-Katibat al-Tawhid wal Jihad (Uzbek) and Junud al-Sham (Chechen) all coordinate with Al-Qaeda affiliate Jabhat Al-Nusra in Syria.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Lister |first=Charles |date=11 September 2015 |title=Al-Qa'ida Plays a Long Game in Syria |journal=Combating Terrorism Center Sentinel |publisher=Combating Terrorism Center |volume=8 |issue=9 |pages=13–18 |doi=|access-date=18 September 2015 |url=https://www.ctc.usma.edu/posts/al-qaida-plays-a-long-game-in-syria}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://thelineofsteel.weebly.com/analysis/katibat-al-tawhid-wal-jihad-involved-in-jisr-al-shughur-fight |title=Katibat al Tawhid wal Jihad involved in Jisr al Shughur fight |work=The Line of Steel m |date=5 October 2015}}</ref> Members of TIP have been killed in battle in Syria.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thelineofsteel.weebly.com/social-media-analysis/turkestan-islamic-party-fighters-killed-in-syria |title=Turkestan Islamic Party Fighters Killed In Syria |work=The Line of Steel |date=7 July 2015}}</ref> TIP (ETIM) eulogized and applauded members of its organization who participated in suicide bombings and members who were killed in action in Jisr al Shughur.<ref>{{cite web |title=Turkistan Islamic Party in Syria conducted suicide bombings at Jisr al Shughur |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/07/turkistan-islamic-party-in-syria-conducted-suicide-bombing-at-jisr-al-shughur.php |website=Long War Journal |date=20 July 2015 |first=Caleb |last=Weiss}}</ref> Members of the group helped other Jihadists enforce religious law in Idlib such as wrecking alcohol in stores and this was noted that with "support of Allah and by the strike of the fist of the Mujahideen from the Al Nusrah Front, [[Ahrar al Sham]] and Turkistan," that they undertook these actions by a Syrian Jihadist in [[Army of Conquest|Jaysh al Fateh]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Jihadist front established to represent foreign fighters in Syria |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/07/jihadist-front-established-to-represent-foreign-fighters-in-syria.php |website=Long War Journal |date=20 July 2015 |first=Thomas |last=Joscelyn}}</ref> A Jabhat Al Nusra Jihadist called Abu Mohamed Al-Ansari interviewed by VICE News after the Idlib offensive said that "The battle was good, praise be to God. The brothers from all the groups started working together and coordinating. Each faction is responsible for a side. The majority were immigrant brothers from Turkestan. They are the ones who attacked the important points."<ref>{{cite av media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d-2uvKfYGQ4 |title=Jihadists vs. the Assad Regime: Syria's Rebel Advance |date=26 May 2015 |work=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=27 May 2015 |title=Jihadists vs. the Assad Regime: Syria's Rebel Advance |url=https://news.vice.com/video/jihadists-vs-the-assad-regime-syrias-rebel-advance |work=Vice News}}</ref> The spokesman of Jabhat Al-Nusra Abu Maria al-Qahtani claimed that Muslims were "oppressed" in "Turkestan" and that Nusra needs to "defend" them.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://imgur.com/u077b4m |title=Imgur: The most awesome images 