{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = Whatever Happened to Interracial Love? | image = Whatever Happened to Interracial Love.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = [[Kathleen Collins]] | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[United States]] | language = English | series = | release_number = | subject = | genre = [[Fiction]], [[short story]] | set_in = | publisher = | publisher2 = | pub_date = [[2016 in literature|2016]] | english_pub_date = | published = | media_type = | pages = 175 pp<ref name=NYT/> | awards = | isbn = 978-0-06-248415-4 | isbn_note = (Paperback) | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = }}
'''''Whatever Happened to Interracial Love?''''' is a [[wikt:Special:Search/posthumous|posthumous]] 2016 collection of short stories by author [[Kathleen Collins]]. The title story was published by ''[[Granta]]'' in July 2016.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Collins|first1=Kathleen|title=Whatever Happened to Interracial Love?|url=https://granta.com/whatever-happened-to-interracial-love/|work=Granta|issue=136: Legacies of Love|date=July 13, 2015|accessdate=September 5, 2016}}</ref>
==Critical reception== ''[[The New York Times]]'' wrote "The best of these stories are a [[revelation]]. Ms. Collins had a gift for illuminating what the critic Albert Murray called the ‘black intramural class struggle,’ and two or three of her stories are so sensitive and sharp and political and sexy I suspect they will be widely anthologized."<ref name=NYT>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/29/books/kathleen-collinss-whatever-happened-to-interracial-love.html|title=Kathleen Collins's ‘Whatever Happened to Interracial Love?’|author=Garner, Dwight|authorlink=Dwight Garner (critic)|date=November 29, 2016}}</ref>
Claire Fallon of ''[[HuffPost]]'' praised the book saying "in poignant, searching scenes and contemplations, readers will be reintroduced to a great and under-appreciated creative talent in Kathleen Collins."<ref name=HP>{{cite web|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=December 2, 2016|title=‘Whatever Happened To Interracial Love?’ Asks Questions We’re Still Trying To Answer|author=Fallon, Claire|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/whatever-happened-to-interracial-love_us_5840aee7e4b09e21702ddb0f}}</ref>
